charmed_rust-dnt: [PropTest] Property-based testing for input parsing

## Objective
Create comprehensive proptest generators for mouse event byte sequences to enable property-based testing of mouse input parsing. This covers SGR, X10, and normal mouse tracking modes.

## Detailed Requirements

### 1. Mouse Button Generators

```rust
use proptest::prelude::*;
use proptest::arbitrary::Arbitrary;

/// Mouse button representation
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum MouseButton {
    Left,
    Middle,
    Right,
    WheelUp,
    WheelDown,
    WheelLeft,
    WheelRight,
    Button4,
    Button5,
    None,  // For motion-only events
}

impl Arbitrary for MouseButton {
    type Parameters = ();
    type Strategy = BoxedStrategy<Self>;

    fn arbitrary_with(_: Self::Parameters) -> Self::Strategy {
        prop_oneof![
            Just(MouseButton::Left),
            Just(MouseButton::Middle),
            Just(MouseButton::Right),
            Just(MouseButton::WheelUp),
            Just(MouseButton::WheelDown),
            Just(MouseButton::WheelLeft),
            Just(MouseButton::WheelRight),
            Just(MouseButton::Button4),
            Just(MouseButton::Button5),
            Just(MouseButton::None),
        ].boxed()
    }
}
```

### 2. Mouse Modifier Generators

```rust
/// Mouse event modifiers
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Default)]
pub struct MouseModifiers {
    pub shift: bool,
    pub alt: bool,
    pub ctrl: bool,
}

impl Arbitrary for MouseModifiers {
    type Parameters = ();
    type Strategy = BoxedStrategy<Self>;

    fn arbitrary_with(_: Self::Parameters) -> Self::Strategy {
        (any::<bool>(), any::<bool>(), any::<bool>())
            .prop_map(|(shift, alt, ctrl)| MouseModifiers { shift, alt, ctrl })
            .boxed()
    }
}

impl MouseModifiers {
    /// Encode modifiers as bits for X10/normal mode
    pub fn to_bits(&self) -> u8 {
        let mut bits = 0u8;
        if self.shift { bits |= 4; }
        if self.alt { bits |= 8; }
        if self.ctrl { bits |= 16; }
        bits
    }
}
```

### 3. SGR Mouse Event Generator

```rust
/// SGR extended mouse event (most modern format)
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct SgrMouseEvent {
    pub button: MouseButton,
    pub modifiers: MouseModifiers,
    pub x: u16,
    pub y: u16,
    pub pressed: bool,  // true = press, false = release
    pub motion: bool,
}

prop_compose! {
    /// Generate SGR mouse event with valid coordinates
    pub fn arb_sgr_mouse_event()(
        button in any::<MouseButton>(),
        modifiers in any::<MouseModifiers>(),
        x in 1u16..=9999,
        y in 1u16..=9999,
        pressed in any::<bool>(),
        motion in any::<bool>(),
    ) -> SgrMouseEvent {
        SgrMouseEvent { button, modifiers, x, y, pressed, motion }
    }
}

impl SgrMouseEvent {
    /// Convert to SGR escape sequence bytes
    /// Format: ESC [ < Cb ; Cx ; Cy M/m
    pub fn to_bytes(&self) -> Vec<u8> {
        let cb = self.encode_button();
        let final_char = if self.pressed { 'M' } else { 'm' };

        format!("\x1B[<{};{};{}{}", cb, self.x, self.y, final_char)
            .into_bytes()
    }

    fn encode_button(&self) -> u8 {
        let base = match self.button {
            MouseButton::Left => 0,
            MouseButton::Middle => 1,
            MouseButton::Right => 2,
            MouseButton::WheelUp => 64,
            MouseButton::WheelDown => 65,
            MouseButton::WheelLeft => 66,
            MouseButton::WheelRight => 67,
            MouseButton::Button4 => 128,
            MouseButton::Button5 => 129,
            MouseButton::None => 3,
        };

        let mut cb = base + self.modifiers.to_bits();
        if self.motion { cb |= 32; }
        cb
    }
}
```

### 4. X10 Mouse Event Generator

```rust
/// X10 compatibility mouse event (legacy format)
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct X10MouseEvent {
    pub button: MouseButton,
    pub x: u8,  // Limited to 223 in X10 mode
    pub y: u8,
}

prop_compose! {
    /// Generate X10 mouse event (limited coordinate range)
    pub fn arb_x10_mouse_event()(
        button in prop_oneof![
            Just(MouseButton::Left),
            Just(MouseButton::Middle),
            Just(MouseButton::Right),
        ],
        x in 1u8..=223,  // X10 limit: 255 - 32 = 223
        y in 1u8..=223,
    ) -> X10MouseEvent {
        X10MouseEvent { button, x, y }
    }
}

impl X10MouseEvent {
    /// Convert to X10 escape sequence bytes
    /// Format: ESC [ M Cb Cx Cy (raw bytes, +32 encoding)
    pub fn to_bytes(&self) -> Vec<u8> {
        let cb = match self.button {
            MouseButton::Left => 0,
            MouseButton::Middle => 1,
            MouseButton::Right => 2,
            _ => 3,  // Release/none
        } + 32;

        vec![
            0x1B, b'[', b'M',
            cb,
            self.x + 32,
            self.y + 32,
        ]
    }
}
```

### 5. Normal Mode Mouse Event Generator

```rust
/// Normal mode mouse event (with modifiers)
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct NormalMouseEvent {
    pub button: MouseButton,
    pub modifiers: MouseModifiers,
    pub x: u8,
    pub y: u8,
    pub motion: bool,
}

prop_compose! {
    pub fn arb_normal_mouse_event()(
        button in any::<MouseButton>(),
        modifiers in any::<MouseModifiers>(),
        x in 1u8..=223,
        y in 1u8..=223,
        motion in any::<bool>(),
    ) -> NormalMouseEvent {
        NormalMouseEvent { button, modifiers, x, y, motion }
    }
}

impl NormalMouseEvent {
    pub fn to_bytes(&self) -> Vec<u8> {
        let mut cb = match self.button {
            MouseButton::Left => 0,
            MouseButton::Middle => 1,
            MouseButton::Right => 2,
            MouseButton::WheelUp => 64,
            MouseButton::WheelDown => 65,
            _ => 3,
        };

        cb += self.modifiers.to_bits();
        if self.motion { cb |= 32; }

        vec![
            0x1B, b'[', b'M',
            cb + 32,
            self.x + 32,
            self.y + 32,
        ]
    }
}
```

### 6. Unified Mouse Event Generator

```rust
/// Any mouse event format
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub enum AnyMouseEvent {
    Sgr(SgrMouseEvent),
    X10(X10MouseEvent),
    Normal(NormalMouseEvent),
}

impl Arbitrary for AnyMouseEvent {
    type Parameters = ();
    type Strategy = BoxedStrategy<Self>;

    fn arbitrary_with(_: Self::Parameters) -> Self::Strategy {
        prop_oneof![
            arb_sgr_mouse_event().prop_map(AnyMouseEvent::Sgr),
            arb_x10_mouse_event().prop_map(AnyMouseEvent::X10),
            arb_normal_mouse_event().prop_map(AnyMouseEvent::Normal),
        ].boxed()
    }
}

impl AnyMouseEvent {
    pub fn to_bytes(&self) -> Vec<u8> {
        match self {
            Self::Sgr(e) => e.to_bytes(),
            Self::X10(e) => e.to_bytes(),
            Self::Normal(e) => e.to_bytes(),
        }
    }
}
```

### 7. Edge Case Generators

```rust
prop_compose! {
    /// Generate mouse events at coordinate boundaries
    pub fn arb_boundary_mouse_event()(
        x in prop_oneof![Just(1u16), Just(255), Just(256), Just(9999)],
        y in prop_oneof![Just(1u16), Just(255), Just(256), Just(9999)],
        button in any::<MouseButton>(),
    ) -> SgrMouseEvent {
        SgrMouseEvent {
            button,
            modifiers: MouseModifiers::default(),
            x, y,
            pressed: true,
            motion: false,
        }
    }
}

prop_compose! {
    /// Generate malformed mouse sequences
    pub fn arb_malformed_mouse()(
        kind in 0u8..=5,
        data in prop::collection::vec(any::<u8>(), 0..10),
    ) -> Vec<u8> {
        match kind {
            0 => vec![0x1B, b'[', b'M'],           // Truncated X10
            1 => vec![0x1B, b'[', b'M', 0],        // Partial X10
            2 => vec![0x1B, b'[', b'<'],           // Truncated SGR
            3 => b"\x1B[<0;1;1".to_vec(),          // Missing final char
            4 => b"\x1B[<0;1;1Z".to_vec(),         // Invalid final char
            _ => data,                              // Random bytes
        }
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

1. **Format Coverage**: Generators exist for all mouse tracking modes:
   - [ ] SGR extended mode (CSI < ... M/m)
   - [ ] X10 compatibility mode (CSI M Cb Cx Cy)
   - [ ] Normal mode with modifiers
   - [ ] UTF-8 extended mode

2. **Event Coverage**: All mouse event types are represented:
   - [ ] Button press (left, middle, right)
   - [ ] Button release
   - [ ] Wheel events (up, down, left, right)
   - [ ] Motion events (with and without button held)
   - [ ] Extended buttons (4, 5, etc.)
   - [ ] Modifier combinations (shift, alt, ctrl)

3. **Coordinate Coverage**:
   - [ ] Valid coordinate ranges for each mode
   - [ ] Boundary values (1, 223, 255, 9999)
   - [ ] Coordinate overflow handling

4. **Serialization**: Each event type has bidirectional conversion:
   - [ ] `to_bytes()` for generating test input
   - [ ] `from_bytes()` for parsing verification

5. **Edge Cases**: Malformed sequence generators for robustness

## Implementation Notes

- Place generators in `crates/bubbletea/src/proptest/generators/mouse.rs`
- X10 and normal modes have limited coordinate range (223 max due to +32 encoding)
- SGR mode supports unlimited coordinates (decimal encoding)
- Motion events set bit 5 (32) in the button byte
- Wheel events use button codes 64-67
- Consider platform differences in mouse handling

